116235376.review:
Darksiders III is a somewhat disappointing entry in an awesome series, but still can be enjoyable. One of the big negatives is simplistic and monotonous gameplay. It is interesting and pleasant, I can easily recommend it for fans of the series and to curious gamers.

Pros:
- Great level design;
- Diverse enemy roster;
- Good controls;
- Amazing enemy design;
- Great visuals;
- Interesting story;
- Awesome art style;
- Good voice acting and soundtrack;
- Decent optimisation;
- Awesome boss fights;

Cons:
- Uninspired gameplay;
- Poor move set;

98236698.review:
Run of the mill action-platformer RPG. Not much else to say.

[u]GOOD[/u]: 
- Action is entertaining enough; 
- Puzzles aren't frustrating (except one from the DLC);

[u]BAD[/u]
- Story's the weakest of the franchise so far (I still haven't played Genesis yet);
- Awful navigation, so to speak, it's just a dot on what's supposed to be a compass. Not helpful at all.

[u]UGLY(ish)[/u]
- No map, but maybe because it not that big;

[hr][/hr] 
Thumbs up because, even with it's flaws, I had fun.

94850583.review:
it's a great game, please don't mind the people complaining about the combat

if you enjoy:
-metroidvania level design with beautiful environments and optional areas to explore;
-combat based on dodge timings and counterattacks;
-learning the bosses attack patterns;

and you don't mind a few inconveniences (no map or controller button changes) and its budget constraints holding it back from reaching its full potential, then you'll have a good time, i sure did
